reviewText: This movie is way worse than that piece of crap The Little Cars. Everything about this movie is just putrid, but do you know why? Tha *@#$ pink car!! I wanted to blow that annoying b**** up>_< Could whoever that made this crud have picked a more annoying voice for 1 of its 2 female cars? I wish igor or whatever that truck was at the end would have destroyed her. Plus shes an idiot. Sparky, Rusty, or whatever that main red car name is, is no better. Ug! So whiny. The father and maybe that slutty green truck were the only ones whos voice didn't make me want to drive nails into my head. The animation is just terrible. I've seen way better animation on Aniboon. Company's like Disney, Dreamworks, and Don Bluth worked for a reason. They didn't just slap crap together and think kids would love anything. Some fools might even argue its for kids, but thats no excuse for how poorly made it is and how obviously it rips off Cars to some extent. I must also add that even though some animated movies do put some adult content in there, this movie does in a way thats just wrong on so many levels. Disney has some crazy, messed up villians that do terrible things, but this movie does it in a way thats just bad (not the good bad).Save your money peaple/parents and if you're curious of how terrible this is just watch it on youtube. Trust me theres better things you could do with your money.

reviewText: This a very low key and very small movie that your kids will love! I grow up when I was little kid seeing cartoon movies and tv shows like this! reviewText: This is the second time I have written this review.  Hopefully it will make it through this time.  My children of 3 and 5 love cars of all sorts.  I purchased this movie based on the other review.  The themes are appropriate for adolescents only.  The characters are ridiculous and flat and predictable.  We could not even finish watching it.  One of the cars is a disturbing character who scared my children.  She is constantly showing up trying to mislead the main protagonist who apparently never learns a lesson (until the very end of course).  It is so predictable, boring and disturbing please don't buy this movie; wait for the real thing to come out.

reviewText: Who is this movie for? The characters and humor could only appeal to very small children, but the subject matter is adolescence. There are any number of interchanges between between the characters that are not appropriate for little kids (for example, when the father car insists that the son car take a bath and the son shouts "child abuse!"), and the villain continually talks about death and is trying to kill the other cars. Add to that the fact that the movie features one of the most annoying voices ever recorded and one full minute of a car driving in circles and screaming and you have one of the worst children's movies that you're ever likely to see. Not recommended for anyone except fans of the bizarre.
